events.text: I stay updated with new technologies through a mix of learning and hands-on practice. I regularly read official documentation, developer blogs, and community forums like Stack Overflow or GitHub discussions to understand trends and solutions to real problems.  I also like to experiment by building small projects or trying out new libraries and frameworks, which helps me understand how they work in practice. Additionally, I follow tech talks, webinars, and tutorials to get insights from experienced developers and keep track of emerging best practices.
